Papa John's International, Inc.

2002 Papa Johns Boulevard 
Louisville KY 40299 United States
Phone: +1 502-___-____
Fax: +1 502-___-____
http://www.papajohns.com





123
Managers




130
IT employees




$70.9MEST.
IT Budget




Papa John's was founded in 1984 as a restaurant chain that specializes in making and delivering pizzas. There are more than 4,000 locations worldwide, and the company operates as the third largest pizza delivery chain in the United States.
IT Priorities:
•The IT department at Papa John's International is heavily focused on maintaining the infrastructure and architecture supporting the company's online ordering, point of sales, and business intelligence systems.
•The company is currently working to develop a new version of its… MoreIT Priorities:
•The IT department at Papa John's International is heavily focused on maintaining the infrastructure and architecture supporting the company's online ordering, point of sales, and business intelligence systems.
•The company is currently working to develop a new version of its proprietary point of sales system, PROFIT, which is utilized across all North American locations.

IT Structure:
•Papa John's IT department, known as Information Services, not only covers US IT operations from headquarters but international IT as well. All major global spending originates from this one office.
•A Digital Technology team operates outside of the IT department, but collaborates closely in developing strategy and systems for new innovations within the company.

IT Vendors:
•The company utilizes third party vendors for a large portion of the company's infrastructure.

IT Intelligence Snippets:
2013:
•The company completed a number of upgrades to its data center systems, including a migration from IBM to EMC VMAX SAN, the installation of Data Domain, and installation of new Brocade switches.
•The company uses Citrix's GoToMeeting application as a communication tool, cutting annual travel costs, increasing employee efficiency and enhancing franchisee satisfaction. The company also uses Radware solutions to bolster eCommerce.
•The company primarily utilizes EMC systems for its data center operations, with Cisco and Blackberry systems managing the voice and data networks.

2012:
•The company updated its PROFIT point of sales system, and decided against moving onto a third party solution.





